<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="012" project="code-quality-and-assurance-r2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Segregate IDataverseService into 9 Domain-Focused Interfaces</title>
    <phase>2: Backend Structural Decomposition</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-hours>5</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies></dependencies>
    <blocks>013</blocks>
    <tags>refactoring, dotnet, architecture</tags>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Segregate IDataverseService (603 lines, 63 methods) into 9 domain-specific interfaces
    following the Interface Segregation Principle. Make IDataverseService a composite interface
    that inherits all 9. Update both concrete implementations (DataverseServiceClientImpl and
    DataverseWebApiService) to implement the composite interface. This must be a zero-breaking-change
    refactor — all existing code that depends on IDataverseService continues to compile and
    behave identically.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer specializing in SOLID principles and service decomposition</role>

  <goal>
    Nine domain-specific interface files exist under src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/.
    IDataverseService inherits all 9. Both DataverseServiceClientImpl and DataverseWebApiService
    implement the composite interface. dotnet build and dotnet test both pass with zero errors
    or failures.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      IDataverseService defines 63 methods across 603 lines covering documents, analysis,
      generic entity operations, processing jobs, events, field mappings, KPIs, communications,
      and health checks. Any service that needs only document operations must still declare a
      dependency on the full 63-method interface, increasing coupling and making mock setup in
      tests unnecessarily verbose. The Interface Segregation Principle (ISP) requires that clients
      depend only on the methods they actually use. The refactoring strategy is additive: create 9
      narrow interfaces, move method signatures into them, then make IDataverseService inherit
      all 9. Both existing implementations continue to implement IDataverseService (the composite)
      and therefore implement all 9 narrow interfaces automatically. No DI registrations need to
      change in this task — that migration happens in task 013.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/IDataverseService.cs (modify — add inheritance chain)</file>
      <file>src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/IDocumentDataverseService.cs (create)</file>
      <file>src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/IAnalysisDataverseService.cs (create)</file>
      <file>src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/IGenericEntityService.cs (create)</file>
      <file>src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/IProcessingJobService.cs (create)</file>
      <file>src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/IEventDataverseService.cs (create)</file>
      <file>src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/IFieldMappingDataverseService.cs (create)</file>
      <file>src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/IKpiDataverseService.cs (create)</file>
      <file>src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/ICommunicationDataverseService.cs (create)</file>
      <file>src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/IDataverseHealthService.cs (create)</file>
      <file>src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/DataverseServiceClientImpl.cs (modify — implement composite)</file>
      <file>src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/DataverseWebApiService.cs (modify — implement composite)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-003">
      The refactoring must be purely additive — zero breaking changes to existing consumers.
      IDataverseService must remain a valid type that all current code can continue to use without
      modification. Do not remove any method signatures from IDataverseService itself; instead
      move them into narrow interfaces and have IDataverseService inherit those interfaces so the
      combined surface area is identical.
    </constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-003.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">
      Read IDataverseService.cs in full. Catalog all 63 methods grouped by domain. Verify the
      following assignment before creating any files:
      IDocumentDataverseService (13 methods) — document CRUD and relationship queries;
      IAnalysisDataverseService (4 methods) — analysis records and outputs;
      IGenericEntityService (9 methods) — generic CRUD and metadata operations;
      IProcessingJobService (8 methods) — Office processing job lifecycle;
      IEventDataverseService (9 methods) — events, logs, and event types;
      IFieldMappingDataverseService (7 methods) — field mapping and record operations;
      IKpiDataverseService (2 methods) — KPI assessments;
      ICommunicationDataverseService (9 methods) — communications and lookups;
      IDataverseHealthService (2 methods) — health checks.
      Adjust the assignment if the actual method groupings differ — document any deviations.
    </step>
    <step order="2">
      Create IDocumentDataverseService.cs with the 13 document-related method signatures.
      Include the correct namespace and any required using statements.
    </step>
    <step order="3">
      Create IAnalysisDataverseService.cs with the 4 analysis-related method signatures.
    </step>
    <step order="4">
      Create IGenericEntityService.cs with the 9 generic entity method signatures.
    </step>
    <step order="5">
      Create IProcessingJobService.cs with the 8 processing job method signatures.
    </step>
    <step order="6">
      Create IEventDataverseService.cs with the 9 event-related method signatures.
    </step>
    <step order="7">
      Create IFieldMappingDataverseService.cs with the 7 field mapping method signatures.
    </step>
    <step order="8">
      Create IKpiDataverseService.cs with the 2 KPI method signatures.
    </step>
    <step order="9">
      Create ICommunicationDataverseService.cs with the 9 communication method signatures.
    </step>
    <step order="10">
      Create IDataverseHealthService.cs with the 2 health check method signatures.
    </step>
    <step order="11">
      Update IDataverseService.cs. Change the interface declaration to:
        public interface IDataverseService :
            IDocumentDataverseService,
            IAnalysisDataverseService,
            IGenericEntityService,
            IProcessingJobService,
            IEventDataverseService,
            IFieldMappingDataverseService,
            IKpiDataverseService,
            ICommunicationDataverseService,
            IDataverseHealthService
      Remove the method signatures from IDataverseService that are now declared in the 9
      interfaces. The body of IDataverseService should contain only the inheritance list.
    </step>
    <step order="12">
      Verify DataverseServiceClientImpl.cs and DataverseWebApiService.cs — confirm they already
      implement IDataverseService (the composite). If their class declarations say
      ": IDataverseService" they automatically implement all 9 narrow interfaces; no changes are
      needed unless the compiler reports missing members. Fix any missing member errors.
    </step>
    <step order="13">
      Run dotnet build from the repository root. Fix all compilation errors.
    </step>
    <step order="14">
      Run dotnet test. Verify all tests pass — this refactoring must not change any behavior.
    </step>
    <step order="15">
      Update projects/code-quality-and-assurance-r2/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md — mark task 012 complete.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output type="file">src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/IDocumentDataverseService.cs</output>
    <output type="file">src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/IAnalysisDataverseService.cs</output>
    <output type="file">src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/IGenericEntityService.cs</output>
    <output type="file">src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/IProcessingJobService.cs</output>
    <output type="file">src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/IEventDataverseService.cs</output>
    <output type="file">src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/IFieldMappingDataverseService.cs</output>
    <output type="file">src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/IKpiDataverseService.cs</output>
    <output type="file">src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/ICommunicationDataverseService.cs</output>
    <output type="file">src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/IDataverseHealthService.cs</output>
    <output type="file">src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/IDataverseService.cs (modified)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>9 focused interface files are created in src/server/shared/Spaarke.Dataverse/</criterion>
    <criterion>IDataverseService inherits all 9 domain interfaces and contains no method signatures of its own</criterion>
    <criterion>DataverseServiceClientImpl implements all 9 narrow interfaces (via composite)</criterion>
    <criterion>DataverseWebApiService implements all 9 narrow interfaces (via composite)</criterion>
    <criterion>Zero breaking changes — no existing consumer files are modified in this task</criterion>
    <criterion>dotnet build passes with zero errors</criterion>
    <criterion>dotnet test passes with all tests green</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
